# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — Francis Farm-Values replication
# =============================================================================
# Everything downloaded by the pipeline, plus everything written by the
# analysis scripts, stays out of git. The only data committed is the
# hand-built free-slave state border shapefile in Data/Border/1820_border/.
# =============================================================================

# --- API keys ---------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.Renviron

# --- Downloaded inputs ------------------------------------------------------
# IPUMS NHGIS data (census tables + shapefiles): cannot be redistributed under
# the IPUMS Terms of Use, so it stays out of git and is downloaded by step 1.
Data/*
!Data/Border/
Data/Border/*
!Data/Border/1820_border/
Data/Border/1820_border/*
!Data/Border/1820_border/*.cpg
!Data/Border/1820_border/*.dbf
!Data/Border/1820_border/*.prj
!Data/Border/1820_border/*.qmd
!Data/Border/1820_border/*.shp
!Data/Border/1820_border/*.shx

# --- Shipped geographic covariates ------------------------------------------
# Geology_v2 holds the pinned county-mean topography (USGS 3DEP/NED) and soil
# texture (CONUS-SOIL) CSVs that 04_Analysis_Spatial_RDD.R reads. These are
# derived from public-domain US-government sources, are only ~3 MB, and are
# committed so the package reproduces Tables 2 and 3 without an OpenTopo key
# or exposure to upstream API drift. Regenerate with 00_Build_Geology_v2.R.
!Data/Geology_v2/
!Data/Geology_v2/**
# ...but not the per-state build checkpoints (intermediate; regenerated on rebuild)
Data/Geology_v2/_state_partials/

# --- Pipeline outputs -------------------------------------------------------
Output/

# --- R session files --------------------------------------------------------
.Rhistory
.RData
.Rproj.user/
*.Rproj

# --- macOS / editor cruft ---------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
